This paper deals with data transfer in opportunistic Delay Tolerant Networks (DTNs), which is a subfield of computer networking. The paper proposes algorithms for optimal forwarding in DTNs, which involves decision-making and resource allocation, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves the estimation of meeting rates, which is a statistical inference problem, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.PF (Performance).
